There r two type of different group of people in today's world, one group of people is always tend to give respect to others who have their own history n civilization while on the other hand tend to give disrespect to the other even though they have their history n civilization.   Manipur is home for different group of people among those only meitei have their own recorded history n civilization. The meitei itslef is the amalgamation of different tribes from different places since prehistoric time.   Every civilization has different time period likewise meitei civilization also has the same that's y there r 3 different historical time period in meitei civilization i;e ancient,medieval n modern.   Here is the origin of meitei n their civilization :   According to ancient text "ÍØÄÍØ•ÍØ°ÍØïÍØÇÍØ£ÍØÖ" (kangbalon);   Ancient manipur(king kangba) before christ : Tang was the 14th generation ruler of a tribe known as Qi who inhabited the central part of present day china. He founded the shang dynasty in 1523BC ~~1027 BC therefore also known as tang-shang dynasty by ancient meiteis. They were known as the upper or higher class group of people. They domesticated horses n used them for transportation. The ruler paid due attention to the agriculture. They also developed glazed potters,silk weaving n making of bronze vessels. It appeared that a group of people from tang-shang dynasty might have move west following yangtze river n later came down the ningthi turel (chindwind river now in myanmar) passed through somra hill range n settled somewhere at the origin of eril river in manipur. After settling there for many years, a leader from that group followed the eril river n reached koubru hill ranges to the northwest(nearly 35km) of present day imphal. The tang-shang people settled along with the LEI-HOU tribe(forefathers of present day kabui,tangkhul,paomai,mao,etc except kuki)an asiatic tibeto~~ burman group who were inhabitants of koubru. That's y valley people called hill people as HOU/HAO even today(from leihou/leihao to hou/hao). From this koubru ranges meitei started flourished their civilization by allowing different tribes to amalgamate in the meitei society.   That's y metei people considered koubru as their sacred place as they started flourished their civilization there since prehistoric time. Meitei has the right to construct their temple at koubru to preserve their heritage. Gandhis point of view --  Congress to b terminated after independance, partition could b avoided by making Jinnah PM ,  As Jinnah was about to die after 6 month after independance due to illness, which was not agreed by Nehru ,who spoke bad about Jinnah making him more aggressive for partition . Jinnah was about to agree to avoid partition if he got PM post , which he cancelled later on due to Nehru remarks and disagreement.  Gandhi had no role to play after independance ,  Gandhi supported decision of giving first instalment to Pakistan ,from govt fund as per partition agreement , for support of Pak govt to poor in Pak.
